#   STATUS tickets: the worktree status view

`be status` (and bare `be`) report the worktree against its baseline as one `status:` ROWS hunk. Tickets here extend that view — the `!`/`--force` extended mode and path/submodule scoping — all on the shared ROWS state banner ([BE-005]). Each entry is one active ticket; it drops off once the whole ticket lands. The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [STATUS-002] — `be status:<sub>/` ignores only the sub's own `.gitignore`, so
    the parent repo's patterns miss submodule paths (flood of `unk build-debug/...`).
    Fix: hierarchical `.gitignore` (cwd→$HOME, compounding, crossing sub
    boundaries) in `dog/git/IGNO`. POST-020 refuted; prior build/Corpus stop-gap
    rejected. Reproduced; rerun in progress.

STATUS-001 (`be status!` ≡ `be status --force` = extended status: file rows PLUS all
tracked branches + remotes, rehoming `SNIFFGetSummary` orphaned by GET-026; plus
`be status:<path>/` sub-scope) landed `bc5c0bd4`. Topic closed.

